<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] To be clear all these numbers are fake, bu=
t this is the mechanism the SEC complaint describes. =E2=80=9COver time, an=
 understanding developed on the part of the Rebalancing Brokers that whenev=
er Melchiorre placed an order to sell one of the AMI Bonds for a Client, he=
 would repurchase it for another Client, either directly the following day =
or days, or indirectly through another broker. =E2=80=A6 The Rebalancing Br=
okers stood to benefit from the Rebalancing Trades because they expected Ch=
atham to repurchase the bonds at a higher price, and it typically did so. M=
elchiorre proposed the price for the Rebalancing Trades and the Rebalancing=
 Brokers agreed to it without first soliciting bids from other market parti=
cipants. When proposing a price for Rebalancing Trades, Melchiorre consider=
ed a number of factors, which included the prior day=E2=80=99s price as ref=
lected in prices published by a pricing service. Those published prices wou=
ld have been influenced, to some extent, by Chatham=E2=80=99s own trading. =
When purchasing the AMI Bonds, Melchiorre also added a spread to compensate=
 the Rebalancing Brokers. For example, in the case of a Rebalancing Trade e=
xecuted through a single Rebalancing Broker overnight, Chatham would repurc=
hase the AMI Bonds for a small spread above what it had sold the AMI Bonds =
to the broker the day before.=E2=80=9D </p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/34124062.285400/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTgvY29pbmJhc2UtdHJhZGVzLWJlYW5pZS1iYWJpZXM_Y21w=
