=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">
talked about this the other day</a> in connection with crypto. I wrote: =E2=
=80=9CAll the downsides of stock =E2=80=94 the fiduciary duties, the sharin=
g of the value of the business, the disclosure obligations =E2=80=94 are no=
t incidental; they are not just arbitrary punishments visited on entreprene=
urs who issue stock. They=E2=80=99re the point. The reason that entrepreneu=
rs can raise money by issuing stock =E2=80=94 they can get real dollars in =
exchange for pieces of paper saying =E2=80=98this is a share of a business =
that doesn=E2=80=99t exist yet=E2=80=99 =E2=80=94 is that there is a highly=
 developed system of obligations that reassures investors that those pieces=
 of paper have value. The investors get some rights, some control, some eco=
nomic ownership, some legal and regulatory protections, in exchange for the=
ir money. And that is why they are willing to part with their money.=E2=80=
=9D </p>
</div>
